SUMMARY:DIY Wire Cloches Level 1
DTSTAMP:20260306T004517Z
DTSTART:20260306T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught in partnership with Northwest Perennial Alliance. In thi
	s hands-on workshop learn how to make the wire cloches NPA uses in the Per
	ennial Border at Bellevue Botanical Garden to keep rabbits from eating the
	 plants. They make great plant supports too! Once you learn wiring skills\
	, you can make them any size and style that suits you\, creating something
	 worthy of a place in your garden. We will supply everything you need to m
	ake one medium-sized cloche and you will receive a materials list with inf
	ormation on suppliers and tools. $24.50 BBGS or NPA Member/$35 Non-Member\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/diy-wire-cloches-level-1/
