BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tnGkmvgEaMGGXo-Lgoea0
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260306T004517Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy the towering trees\, listen to the birds\, and give a lit
	tle back to this beautiful park by removing common ivy that is taking over
	  the understory of Pioneer Park's SE quadrant. It will be a great chance 
	t o get your hands in the dirt\, learn about native plants and our local f
	orests\, and work alongside neighbors and friends!\n\nAll ages welcome\, a
	nd no experience necessary! Gloves\, tools\, water\, and small snacks prov
	ided. Please note: we require participants aged 14 and under to volunteer 
	 with a parent or guardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen: Satur
	d ay\, March 7th\, 10am-1pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park SE\, follow volunteer e
	vent signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in clothes you don't mi
	nd get ting dirty \\(think: long pants\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring water
	. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools will be provided.\n\nRegistration: htt
	ps://volunteersignup.org/CWRCR\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/restoration-event-pioneer-park/18066420/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtod
	ay - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer
	-park/18066420/2026-03-07T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tnAJaKzdDKykGpjE9ZPoT
SUMMARY:Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind
DTSTAMP:20260306T004517Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Samantha Yun Wall’s new paintings use overlapping silhouettes o
	f female figures as portals to unknown spaces and different temporal realm
	s. Impetus for the new body of work is a Korean folk tale in which the Pas
	que flower is symbolic of a grandmother who passed away without the loving
	 care of her grandchildren. It is a story of melancholy\, loss\, and remem
	brance. The delicate hair on the flower’s stem differentiates it\, and the
	 artist gives the plant a surreal aspect in some of her paintings\, replac
	ing the flower’s center with a watchful eye.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.c
	om/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we-leave-behind/18026187/2026-0
	3-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we
	-leave-behind/18026187/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:HuHSV_hlaMZUYR2XPvfNJ
SUMMARY:Carnation Farms Meat & Greet: a Hands-on Visit with Sheep and Cattl
	e
DTSTAMP:20260306T004517Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Do you know where your burger comes from? Want to meet your far
	mer? Get ready for a hands-on visit with the adorable sheep and cattle at 
	Carnation Farms. Our farmers will share their expertise\, answer your ques
	tions\, and show you what makes our animals so unique. This is an interact
	ive\, all-ages event perfect for anyone curious about where their food com
	es from\, interested in regenerative farming\, or eager to meet our animal
	s up close.\n\nThis experience is FREE to all interested\, but please regi
	ster so we can know who to expect.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/
	#/details/carnation-farms-meat-greet-a-hands-on-visit-with-sheep-and-cattl
	e/17896493/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/carnation-farms-meat-gree
	t-a-hands-on-visit-with-sheep-and-cattle/17896493/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Carnation Farms\, 28901 Northeast Carnation Farm Road\, Carnation\
	, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
